Introduction

Every time you visit a website, your browser performs several operations behind the scenes in just a few milliseconds.

Although it seems as simple as typing a URL and pressing Enter, your browser has to:

Find the website's server
Establish a connection
Secure the communication
Request the webpage
Receive the response
Display the website

Understanding this process is the first step toward learning Web Security.

